🌟 The Benevolent Triad (Lightwielding)
Focus: Psyche, Restoration, and Transcendence. Often targets Conviction. Common with Clerical or Holy Warrior archtypes.
    1. Purelight: Base type damage of Lightwielding. Raw, searing brilliance that burns similar to fire, but especially hurts characters and monsters prone to dark arts or the undead.
    2. Solacium: A non-lethal "damage" type that forcibly calms the target, draining their "Tenacity" and initiative. 
    3. Aegis Reflection: A concussive, hard-light force reflected from barriers or shields. Can be found naturally emitted from rare objects. A damage type common in auras.
    4. Verdicium: A psychic "truth" strike that deals damage based on the target’s hidden "Scarring" or guilt. Meaning it especially hurts enemies physically that has weak conviction.
    5. Blessed Materium: In rare items, they bypass all physical resistances, and gives physical damage equivalent to the weapons type.
🌍 The Focused Triad (Materium)
Focus: Physical Laws and Elements. Targets Physiology and Hardening. There exists natural synergy effects to spells with all elemental damages where multiple predictable or unpredictable damages can happen. Earthen magic is also deeply connected to Athropium and Tempus. Common in elementalism, shamanism and witchcraft and is often the base for all magic wielders in some form.
    6. Impact (Base type of damage of materium): Pure, invisible physical force; the "universal" language of moving matter.
    7. Earthen: Earth elemental damage. Vibrational earth energy that shatters bone and stone; ignores light armor or in extreme forms: Generates earth quakes or summon earthern objects or entities.
    8. Tempest: Wind elemental damage. High-pressure wind and atmospheric cutting force; invisible and silent. Also generates an electric rupture that creates a cascade effect that lingers and synergies with other types of damages.
    9. Fire: Thermal heat that melts, burns and shapes; the "natural" fire of the physical world. Simple but can be incredibly deadly in the hand of an expert.
    10.  Aquas: The heavy, crushing weight of high-velocity water and hydraulic pressure.
    11.  Athropium: Life force and nature type of damage. Attacks the very life force of all things. Common in witchcraft.
    12. Temporal: Time damage, creates aging of both the living and the immaterial. The ability to instantly wither an armor or even kill a foe by aging it. Drains much of the casters materium connection pool. 
🌑 The Malevolent Triad (Shadow Arts)
Focus: Decay, Entropy, and Domination. Targets Vitality and Max HP. Common in necromancy, Voidmagic, Demonoly, witchcraft and with Dark warrior classes.
    12.  Darkvoid: The damaged energy of materium that is very unstable and difficult to control and direkt. 
    13. Chill: An absolute, supernatural cold that saps "Metabolism" and slows physical movement to a crawl. Resisted in synergy with cold resistance and high conviction modifier. 
    14. Blight: Biological decay and rot that targets the "Physiology" stat and mimics rapid aging and creates a side effect of also hurting the biology with lingering effects. Resisted with immunity and not any unique magical resistances.
    15. Darkblood: Attacks the blood of the target for damage or manipulation. Blood is stongly connected to the damaged energies of materium. Always hurt the wielder to a percentage. Resisatance is very rare. But Stone Folks are unusually resilient.
    16. Arcane: The pure energy of materium. Especially dangerous to unarmored targets since it reacts and dwindles quickly against normal steel and iron. This means its usually dangerous to light armored or non armorered targets.
